cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS 

This paper deals with cyber threat intelligence and data science research applied to a specific type of Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attack prevalent in the Domain Name System (DNS). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses data from a globally distributed set of passive collectors (pDNS), which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses statistical classifiers and unsupervised learning, which are techniques used in the categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with time series features, which suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
